Posco Power Says to Join AES’s Power Plant Project in Vietnam

-- B y   S u n g w o o   P a r k
-- 
2011-02-23T07:55:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/posco-power-says-to-join-aes-s-power-plant-project-in-vietnam.html
  Posco  Power Corp., a unit of  South
Korea ’s biggest steelmaker, said it signed a contract with U.S.-
based  AES Corp . to join a project to build  Vietnam ’s Mong Duong
2 power plant.  The power-generation unit of Posco will acquire a 30
percent stake from AES in the coal-fired power plant, Posco
Power said in an e-mailed statement today.  Posco didn’t say how much it would pay for the stake. The
Korean power producer will invest about $153 million by 2015 in
the plant to be built in Quang Ninh in northern Vietnam with a
capacity of 1,200 megawatts, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sungwoo Park in  Seoul  at 
 spark47@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Poole at 
 jpoole4@bloomberg.net  